          "Small savings schemes are run by the government (Ministry of Finance) — rates revised quarterly, sovereign guaranteed, distributed via post offices AND authorised banks",
          "PPF (Public Provident Fund): 15-year lock-in, ₹500 to ₹1.5 lakh/year, ~7.1% tax-free interest, full 80C deduction. EEE (Exempt-Exempt-Exempt) tax status — the gold standard of safe investing",
          "Sukanya Samriddhi Account (SSA): for a girl child below 10 years — highest small-savings rate (~8.2%), 80C benefit, matures at 21 years or marriage after 18. One account per girl",
          "SCSS (Senior Citizen Savings Scheme): for those 60+, 5-year tenure, ~8.2%, max ₹30 lakh, quarterly interest payout — popular retirement income product",
